				Trollslayer pt 1
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				The small caravan slowly creaked along the west karana plains carrying many goods headed for Qeynos. The two warriors hired to guard the caravan kept an ever-present watch on the small hills and huts knowing full well that bandits could strike at any moment. Then it came, a band of troll came running down an embankment yelling war cries. The warriors steadied themselves knowing that without them the caravan would stand no chance of escaping. The first troll struck with a blow knocking the smaller warrior to his back. The troll brought one of his feet on the warrior&#8217;s chest and lifted his sword over the prone warrior&#8217;s chest. The warrior tried to inch his way to his shield. The troll snickered at this attempt and swiftly brought his sword down. The warrior shut his eyes and braced himself. <br>  <br> He opened his eyes and saw that the troll had collapsed. The warrior stood up in shock and saw a steel arrow between the troll&#8217;s eyes. He came back to his senses to see his companion fending off another troll. He ran and with a quick slash cut the back of the troll's knee dropping him for his companion&#8217;s final blow. As his companion's sword swung he heard a heavy thump behind him, he turned to see another dead troll. <br>  <br> &quot;Where's the archer?&quot; he asked. <br>  <br> &quot;Archer?&quot; his companion asked. <br>  <br> &quot;This troll was hit by an archer.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;I don't see anybody&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;Neither do I.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;Don't worry about it we still have two more trolls to deal with.&quot; <br>  <br> The first of the these trolls carried a what was once a trunk of a young tree the swamp mud dried froglok blood still clung to the roots. The small warrior ducked just as the troll swung leaving an open target. He swung and ripped the troll's side open. The troll turned his eyes scowled and swung again hitting the warrior in the ribs. The warrior curled up on the ground coughing blood knowing that he would soon perish whether it be by the beating he would soon face or by the one already inflicted. He shut his eyes and let the wave of blackness engulf him. <br>  <br> He awoke to find his stomach wrapped and a half-elf standing over him. His companion sat by a fire. <br>  <br> &quot;Where am I, who are you?&quot; he asked <br>  <br> &quot;I am Cawlador, a half-elf ranger and you are in the hills of Qeynos.&quot; the half-elf replied <br>  <br> &quot;How did I get here?&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;I shot down the club wielding troll and upon seeing he was alone the last troll fled fortunately for him he was out of range. I then help bandage you and kept an eye on the caravan while you rested.&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;How can I repay you?&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;No payment necessary just be more careful for I will not always be there. Tell me warrior what is your name?&quot; <br>  <br> &quot;Jebin Wolfe.&quot; the young warrior replied <br>  <br> Cawlador then stood and said &quot;Good luck to you good Jebin&quot;  <br>  <br> Before Jebin could respond Cawlador ran into the darkness. Jebin lay back down and shut his eyes. He opened them again when he heard a branch snap. <br> The last troll held his companion high above his head. His companion's head rolled freely back a look of terror etched on his face. <br>  <br> &quot;Now that pesky elf is gone its time for revenge.&quot; The troll boasted <br> 		

